    <item>
      <title>Re: any official word on spell dmg vs. melee dmg?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=6420#M6420</link>
      <description>I wont get too far into opinion, alot of people share the same opinion as me on the previous caster vs melee posts, but some don't.  I'll just stick to the facts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In 2005, druid, wizard, magician, cleric, shaman, necromancer, wizard, and enchanter spells were upgraded to more damage, and/or be more mana efficient. Spells 1-50 did less damage and costed more mana before 2005. They did this to make casters as par with the expansions released up to dragons of norrath.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The thought, and truth behind this was that ever since kunark, melee weapons 1-50 have been upgraded various times, however caster spells always stayed the same. They always did the same damage, and costed the same mana. In 2005, as I stated before, they upgraded spells to do considerably more amounts of damage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This was a great update, everyone I knew including myself loved it. It made alot of sense, probably one of the few great things SoE did for free, however since the topic of a progression server comes up, the spells that were upgraded in 2005, to balence and trivialize casters with melees, are now global across all servers, which holds true in the fact that they'll be held on the new progression server.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What's the problem with this? It's that melees are going to be using old world weapons, and casters are going to be using new world upgraded spells that were meant to put casters at par with the 2005 state of everquest.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's like putting modern engine parts in an old car frame. Casters are going to be on overdrive for a long time with their upgraded spells, untill expansions are released to put melee's back at part with casters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
